Evans Kidero has finally renamed three city roads after Kenyan heroes and heroines and commissioned the construction of Sh6.5 billion roads in a bid to reduce traffic.The Nairobi Governor renamed Forest Road after Wangari Maathai in recognition of the Nobel Laureate's tireless campaigns for a safe environment. It is good to recognise her work. Without Maathai Nairobi would not exist. Land grabbers could have taken Uhuru Park and Karura Forest, Kidero said on Wednesday.Read: Thank you for renaming road after Maathai, says Green BeltCross Road in the CBD was renamed after veteran multi-partyism crusader Charles Rubia. The road between City Hall Annex and Cardinal Otunga Plaza to Uhuru Highway is now Cardinal Otunga Road. Kidero announced the county's plan to rename the roads during Mashujaa Day Celebrations at Pumwani Sports Ground on October 20.The Governor commissioned the expansion of the 800m Accra Road stretch, which connects the CBD to Park Road. The construction of the Sh6.5 billion, eight-kilometre road from Ngara through Gikomba Market to Landhies Road was also ordered.Kidero said the World Bank-funded project was delayed by encroachment on road reserves by small scale traders, jua kali artisans and mechanics. The road will be completed in a year. I appeal to you, allow contractors to do their work when they get to where you are," he told the traders.He noted the work was part of the wider construction of the missing Eastern link.